snippet.textDisplay: You are dreaming or delusional if you're going to try to argue that China's food practices don't contribute to these sorts of illnesses. There's a reason Asia (in particular China) is heavily studied when annual vaccines are being considered. Everything about the way in which they contain, kill, and distribute their livestock increases the likelihood of viral mutation or transmission. To claim this fact (and it is absolutely a fact) is somehow racist is an utter absurdity. Any virologist would laugh in your face. It's not racist to recognize and state "things in X area are like Y, therefore we should be cautious of Z outcome." Stop trying to inject idiotic identity politics into science.

snippet.textDisplay:
❗️IMPORTANT PLEASE READ ❗️
How is the new conornavirus spread and how can I protect myself ?

Hand hygiene is the first and most important line of defence.

Like cold and flu bugs, the new virus is spread via droplets when a person coughs or sneezes. The droplets land on surfaces and are picked up on the hands of others and spread further. People catch the virus when they touch their infected hands to their mouth, nose or eyes.

It follows that the single most important thing you can do to protect yourself is to keep your hands clean by washing them frequently with soap and water or a hand sanitising gel.
